text:
it kinda feels weird hearing this at (almost) its 11th anniversary, how time flies doesn't it?
It's like a time machine that you can wear in only one-hand.
I'm from eleven years in the future and I am hearing this for the first time, so much has changed, and yet so much still remains...
 heh at least 600 Million people have died since this video was uploaded and yet as much as another Billion was born...
Just by looking in the comments its hard to find one that is not at least 5 years old
But here's a lesson for the next eleven years, that hopefully the next time-traveller'll see,
Good things never die.
For internet standards something as "new" as a month "old" is already... "old"
And here I am after at 132 months and almost as 4000 days later...
And I got to say this is a heck of remix, from a heck of a OST from a game that it is 23-24 years old.
Well... if you INDEED are from the future, can you make a favor and reply to me when you see this comment? Not the author himself, anyone that could just say "Hello, Alexandre Kuritza, check this new-old Stickerbush Remix"
I'd be grateful, and I'll be waiting, see you in eleven years!

text:
I'm only a couple months older than this game. Fortunately, I have a brother nine years my senior and a casual dad, so I still managed to grow up with this shit. The very first video game I ever played. Still have the SNES and still play it sometimes, and I don't care if my family thinks I'm weird for just listening to the music, or if I know every damn nook and cranny from playing and from memorizing the player's guide since I was four, I never get tired of it because of the nostalgia.
Sometimes I don't even have to play it. Every time I just remember how much I love this game (and series), I am just filled with so much joy. <3
author: Hannah Banina

text: I was born in 1989 and got my first and only SNES in 1994. I haven't played it in almost 20 years until recently. Like if someone hit the pause button on my life since the last time I played.
